  <heading>REVD</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Reverse 64-bit doublewords in elements (predicated)</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction reverses the order of 64-bit doublewords within
each active element of the source vector,
and places the results in the corresponding elements of the destination vector. 
Inactive elements in the destination vector register remain unmodified or
are set to zero, depending on whether merging or zeroing
predication is selected.</para>
    </authored>
    <predicated>True</predicated>
    <uses_dit condition="FEAT_SVE2 is implemented or FEAT_SME is implemented">True</uses_dit>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
    <operationalnote>
      <operationalnote_content>
        <para>This instruction is a data-independent-time instruction as described in <xref linkend="ARMARM_BEICCDDAB3">About PSTATE.DIT</xref>.</para>
      </operationalnote_content>
    </operationalnote>
  </operationalnotes>
